		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The surest way may be to import an original Famicom cart that uses the MMC3 and same size ROMs.</div><br />Agreed that donor carts are probably the most reliable way to get ASIC mappers other than MMC1.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Actually at the moment I'm not sure where the list is of board types, anyone know?</div>
<br />Subcats of <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Category:Mappers" class="postlink">Cat:Mappers</a>. Tennessee CV used to maintain <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Board_table" class="postlink">a list of boards used by North American games</a>.

		

